Doc,<br><br>
Thanks for your recent post.  I know what that overwhelming  <br>
fear of wanting to stay alive is all about.  We all experienced <br>
it.  Their are all types of reasons that drive us toward decisions <br>
Fear of death, especially if you truely feel the sacrifice to <br>
be futile, is more than most could bare.  I believe we have reached <br>
an honest position about what additive factors influence our <br>
decisions in life.<br><br>
Doc I respect your feelings of fear.  Fear even now drives many of <br>
us on this sight.  It never leaves us.  It is both our friend <br>
and our enemy.  Remember that overwhelming fear does not necessarily <br>
carry the marker of coward.  It is not that simple.  Hell, 30 + years <br>
as a pilot and my fear of heights outside the cockpit is consuming.  <br>
I can not even stand  on a hotel balcony, no matter what the view.<br><br>
Thanks again for what I believe was an honest post.  Lets see where <br>
we go from here.
